text: Smith: We believe the relationship between the democracies of North America and the democracies of Europe is key, in turn, to a stable and prosperous relationship with China and the rest of the world. #ACawards 9///t.co/HeFvMXVsT3

name: Fred Kempe
text: We at @FedEx were profoundly disappointed the US administration ended our country's involvement with TPP, says Smith noting the importance of int'l institutions. Our lack of participation puts American exporters at significant disadvantage. #ACawards 8///t.co/p5bKfeJQhG

name: Fred Kempe
text: On @FedEx's decades-long business in Asia, Smith says China's economic growth has been unprecedented in the history of the world and that opening European & US markets to Chinese exports made it possible. FedEx played a major role in facilitating China's growth. #ACawards 7///t.co/wF7n1UjkPa

name: Fred Kempe
text: The unprecedented door-to-door trade flowing through the international networks of @FedEx has truly changed the way the world works, says Smith. We at FedEx are very proud our major hub in Europe is in France where we are in the midst of a major expansion now. #ACawards 6///t.co/XP3PbN7bA4

text: Next at #ACawards Christine @Lagarde, Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund, will be presented the Council's Distinguished International Leadership Award. Watch live at://t.co/zcJxmJpI0z 1/

name: Fred Kempe
text: The modern strategic relationship between the U.S. and Europe now spans over a century, says Smith, highlighting the long US commitment to its allies in Europe and noting his own military experience in @USMC. #ACawards 5///t.co/bPFFhxY4Yh

name: Fred Kempe
text: Noting @FedEX's large presence in Europe and the importance of France in particular to the company's history, Smith says he is especially proud to be here tonight with one of France's greatest citizens, Christine @Lagarde. #ACawards 4///t.co/PyVxn564B5

name: Fred Kempe
text: I am honored [to accept the Atlantic Council award] representing 450,000 FedEx global team members who earned this award. We are proud to connect people and possibilities everywhere, says Smith. #ACawards 3///t.co/8eWxa9SGKB

name: Fred Kempe
text: Smith, CEO of @FedEx, received his award delivered by the FedEx SameDay Bot, which he says is an example of innovation and creativity that has marked FedEx over its 46 years of operation and there is more to come I can assure you. #ACawards 2///t.co/6y2vByES8n

name: Fred Kempe

Most remarkably, Alexandar says "The founder in 1973 is still the CEO today 46 years later." #ACawards 1///t.co/lTOACyyPOQ

name: Fred Kempe
text: "The challenges we face are no match for the brand of leadership represented by you in this room tonight," says @FredKempe noting the chief executives, chairmen & presidents as well as 5 former heads of state and sitting ministers and four members of Congress. #ACawards 3/end//t.co/ryOtFztYNZ

name: Fred Kempe
text: Laying out the big strategic challenges facing the world, @FredKempe says that at the Council we "don't see any of these challenges as a reason for despair... but we do see this as a call to action. #ACAwards. 2///t.co/1S2rMGBYCS

name: Fred Kempe
text: Council President & CEO @FredKempe opens our #ACawards second half: For nearly 60 years, the Atlantic Council has pursued the mission bestowed upon us by our founders: to galvanize constructive US leadership, alongside our global friends and allies, to shape the future." 1///t.co/sFwHRdnC5t

name: Fred Kempe
text: Thank you for this honor tonight" @AdrienneArsht says. "I ask that you join me in living a life by standing up for what you believe, whatever that may be. #ACawards 9///t.co/xdXFwCVPiy

name: Fred Kempe
text: As gifts to #ACawards guests, @AdrienneArsht has given pocket copies of the US Constitution, which her mother always carried. Inside, she says she added a card quoting Edmund Burke: All that is necessary for the triumph of evil is that good people do nothing.' #ACawards 8///t.co/8rDmMzdD2S

name: Fred Kempe
text: Part of that rent is to care for & support humanity, says @AdrienneArsht. My father always taught me that you only regret your economies. All my philanthropic decisions flow from this. #ACawards 7///t.co/jYm6A2LJer

name: Fred Kempe
text: Accepting the Council's Distinguished Service Award, @AdrienneArsht quotes Muhammad Ali and her friend Alonzo Mourning and says Our time here on earth is a gift. We pay rent for that time. And those of us here in this room live in a very high rent district! #ACawards 6///t.co/cl5Aayx2fJ

name: Fred Kempe
text: On @AdrienneArsht, Alonzo Mourning says "The through line in all of her efforts is fortifying resources: natural, financial, and cultural resources as well as human relationships Adrienne is the quintessential tastemaker." #ACawards 5///t.co/nTjPQCpPC1

name: Fred Kempe
text: Alonzo Mourning, introducing @AdrienneArsht as her long-time personal friend, says The one common thread we all share is that none of us would be here without the contributions of others we have an obligation to pay it forward. #ACawards 4///t.co/jc6f35fBzt

name: Fred Kempe
text: Fred Kempe says the word "historic" was often cut out when he worked for the Wall Street Journal. But, @AdrienneArsht's commitment is historic. 3/ #ACawards//t.co/fXZ2CaMcKx

name: Fred Kempe
text: =Adrienne Arsht challenged us to question the bounds of the human spirit and its inherent resilience, @FredKempe says, as she gives incredible support to the Atlantic Counil programs. Adrienne Arsht has committed $25 million to permanently endow @ACResilience. 2/ #ACawards//t.co/2til6lCFkP

name: Fred Kempe
text: The @AtlanticCouncil gives these awards not only to honor leaders, but to inspire others to step forward and contribute to a better world, says @FredKempe, adding that honoring of @NATO is Lifetime Achievement Award on the alliance's 70th birthday. 1/ #ACawards//t.co/Y0y0SUsls2

name: Fred Kempe
text: Together Europe & North America are greater than the sum of our partshalf the world's economic might & halfthe military might, says @JensStoltenberg. When we stand together we are stronger than any potential challenger economically, politically & militarily. #ACawards 14///t.co/T9dkg6PNsS

name: Fred Kempe
text: Today as we face the biggest security challenges in a generation, Europe and North America are doing more together than for many years, says @JensStoltenberg. Because @NATO is good for Europe and NATO is good for the US. #ACawards 13///t.co/zfzSczYeef

name: Fred Kempe
text: For 70 years, @NATO has ensured unprecedented peace and prosperity, uniting 2 contents, 29 allies, and almost 1 billion people, says @JensStoltenberg. #ACawards 12///t.co/HZGW4osFdv

name: Fred Kempe
text: It is a great honor to receive this Distinguished Leadership Award on behalf of the whole of @NATO, says @JensStoltenberg. NATO is the most successful alliance in history because through the decades we have kept our commitment to protect & defend one another. #ACawards 11///t.co/l4zqMxVX9n

name: Fred Kempe
text: And most of all, @Gottemoeller says thanks for the almost one billion citizens, for whom the outcome is a safer, stronger, more prosperous world. #ACawards #StrongerWithAllies #NATOat70 10///t.co/pqFhgzBWS0

name: Fred Kempe
text: It is a particular honor to be joinedby representatives of @NATO's former & current leadership," says @Gottemoeller. I'm really here to accept this award on behalf of all the incredible men and women who have helped make NATO what it is today. #ACawards 9///t.co/jutTMa3bHn

name: Fred Kempe
text: On signing @NATO's founding treaty in Washington in 1949, Acheson described his hope that new strength and courage would come to all peoples of the world who seek freedom and peace. name: Fred Kempe
text: Accepting on behalf of @NATO, Rose @Gottemoeller thanks @fredkempe, @DamonMacWilson and the entire team at the Atlantic Council for honoring NATO with this prestigious award in our 70th anniversary year. Watch live://t.co/zcJxmJ86BZ #ACawards 7///t.co/TfmxyaC5GW

name: Fred Kempe
text: Rose is a friend to many in this room. She is a well respected career diplomat and one of the finest minds in non-proliferation and arms control, says Jones inviting @NATO's Deputy Secretary General @Gottemoeller to the stage. #ACawards 6///t.co/lzDruGA3WU

name: Fred Kempe
text: Jones: Ellen Tauscher would have been so pleased that her dear friend and successor at @StateDept as Under Secretary, Rose @Gottemoeller, will accept the award on behalf of NATO as the Alliance's Deputy Secretary General. #ACawards 5///t.co/jl6QBYEF2o

name: Fred Kempe
text: Ellen continued to make her mark in policy outside of government, says Jones, noting her service on boards and non-profits, including as Vice Chair of the Atlantic Council's @ACScowcroft. #ACawards 4///t.co/MyQGMN3Pm2

name: Fred Kempe
text: Jones: Ellen Tauscher understood the importance of a strong American foreign policy and quickly became one of the Congress' leading experts on nuclear weapons, non-proliferation, and arms control. #ACawards 3///t.co/BR8Qkmh6Pa

name: Fred Kempe
text: Gen Jones pauses to say a few words to honor Ellen Tauscher, who passed away yesterday, calling her one of NATO's most active advocates. She was a patriot, politician, transatlanticist, Council board director and above all a friend to many of us in the room. #ACawards 2///t.co/oN3iCAedNw

name: Fred Kempe
text: We're gathered to celebrate an individual who exemplifies the leadership, the vision, and the character needed to navigate turbulent times. name: Fred Kempe
text: John Rogers brings to light why NATO's contributions to maintain peace and safety is so significant against that backdrop. "@NATO is a truly deserving organization." 4/ #NATOat70 #ACawards//t.co/FkfCk799S7

name: Fred Kempe

name: Fred Kempe
text: Today, we hope to advance a far more ambitious leadership that is equal to the challenges we collectively place. "At the very heart of this vast change, stands the Atlantic Council." #ACawards 3///t.co/7gTRJQpZSc

text: Standing before you this evening, John Rogers says, I don't need to tell you that together our allies and friends face one of the most geopolitical environments in recent memory. "Seldom has that world has been so acutely in need of authentic leadership." #ACawards 2///t.co/zOsdVhA04P

text: The entire @AtlanticCouncil family mourns the loss the extraordinary Rep. Ellen Tauscher, a member of our board's Executive Committee and Vice Chair of @ACScowcroft. She contributed so much to our nation and our institution. Thank you //t.co/U6FtFZiJ9T

text: When I think of the Atlantic Council, I think of the last decade where the Council itself actually changed to meet the environment we are operating in, says Jones. For the future, its strategic emphasis will keep the Council viable. #ACForum 10/10//t.co/u7YAE7TUBA

name: Fred Kempe
text: The Atlantic Council's @FredKempe asks Rogers and Jones role the organization should play in this increasingly complex international environment. It's a catalyst to help Washington to be as good as we want it to be and maybe better than it is, Rogers says. #ACForum 9///t.co/8jc3DgvSAz

name: Fred Kempe
text: Chairman-elect Rogers: To me, I think the unique aspect of the Atlantic Council is the ability to foster the development of those new institutions, to refine some of the ones that have existedwhat are the capacities that need to be added on for us to be successful? #ACForum 8///t.co/bRXJPVLPlR

name: Fred Kempe
text: I find that you can't divide any more into the neat organizational structure of just economic, just political, just military and that the blending is quite pronounced, says Rogers. The US can't do it alone and has to do it with others. #StrongerWithAllies #ACForum 7///t.co/Q8uXW6Z1bt

name: Fred Kempe
text: Atlantic Council Chairman-elect John F.W. Rogers: I'm in a hybrid of still believing strongly in the economic underpinnings of national security and as I've traveled in the world also seeing evolution is having a dramatic effect at incredible speeds. #ACForum 6///t.co/9qYXHqSUeh

name: Fred Kempe
text: We have to create a set of international norms that shows there are consequences, says Jones. In my judgment appeasement of these competing autocracies is not the way to go. If you give in on one thing they'll take the next step. We could lose this race. #ACForum 5///t.co/VP2ddbGoEE

name: Fred Kempe
text: We live in a world where we face rising autocracies, say Jones. Democracies are either being changed or challenged but our principle challenges are coming from autocracies. Some of them are not backwaterthey're capable of challenging our primacy in this century. #ACForum 4///t.co/Zn9A3JQKzy

name: Fred Kempe
text: I don't think that's the case, Jones says. The question we should really be concerned about is what's the destiny of the 21st century? If you can't change, your domain will fall & you will fail. I think one of the things we need to understand is that we can fail #ACForum 3///t.co/sqOhc80fAi

name: Fred Kempe
text: What keeps you up at night? @FredKempe asks Gen Jones. Great nations, empires all have a beginning and an end, Jones says there's a naive belief in our country that there's some sort of destiny that the primacy of the US is ensured for some reason forever. #ACForum 2///t.co/uO8s1oVVsq
